# Agent Instructions

## Operating Mode
- Treat this repository as production code.
- Inspect before editing.
- Keep changes focused on the requested task.
- Prefer existing patterns, helpers, package managers, and test style.
- Do not commit, push, rewrite history, delete data, or run destructive commands unless explicitly asked.

## Implementation Standard
- Make the smallest complete change that solves the task.
- Preserve public behavior unless the task asks to change it.
- Add or update tests when behavior changes.
- Run the narrowest useful verification first, then broader checks when risk justifies it.
- Call out any skipped verification and why.

## Review Checklist
- Correctness and edge cases
- Type, lint, build, and test failures
- Data migrations and backwards compatibility
- Auth, permissions, secrets, and privacy
- Concurrency, async behavior, caching, and retries
- User-facing copy, accessibility, and responsive layout for frontend changes

## Final Response
- Summarize changed files and behavior.
- Include verification commands and results.
- Mention residual risks or follow-ups.
